LTG H.R. McMaster delivered a speech at the United States Naval Academy on the topic of preparing for in extremis leadership. He emphasized the importance of intellectual, emotional, and ethical preparation for leading teams in challenging and dangerous conditions. McMaster discussed the value of studying history to gain a deeper understanding of war and warfare, as well as the emotional demands of combat. He also highlighted the need for ethical training to ensure moral and ethical conduct in combat. McMaster cited the example of Admiral James Bond Stockdale, who demonstrated exceptional leadership while being held captive in Vietnam. He concluded by urging the future leaders and officers to prepare themselves intellectually, emotionally, and ethically for the challenges they will face in their roles.